a2tools (1.0.0) noble; urgency=medium

  * 1.0.0 release.
  * Licensing:
    - Add MIT license (LICENSE).
    - Update debian/copyright to the Expat (MIT) form.
  * Documentation:
    - Add manpages for every user-facing command: a2sitemgr(1),
      a2certrenew(1), a2wcrecalc(1), a2wcrecalc-dms(1), fqdnmgr(1) and
      fqdncredmgr(1). Installed to /usr/share/man/man1/.

 -- Amine Tbaik <tbaik.amine@gmail.com>  Sun, 05 Jul 2026 00:00:00 +0000

a2tools (0.2) noble; urgency=medium

  * Rearchitecture release.
  * Packaging:
    - Switch to source format 3.0 (native); no orig tarball required.
    - Move scripts out of /usr/bin subdirectories (FHS violation) into
      /usr/lib/a2tools with /usr/bin symlinks; shared data (templates,
      usage texts, SQL schemas) now lives in /usr/share/a2tools.
    - Fix inverted debian/links entries; logrotate snippet now installs to
      the correct path.
    - Add missing runtime dependencies: jq, libxml2-utils. Drop socat,
      cron, openssl, apache2-utils (no longer used).
    - Add postrm: clean state/cache/logs and the certbot hook on purge.
  * Scheduling:
    - Replace broken cron files (wrong paths, dotted filenames skipped by
      run-parts) with a systemd timer for domain DB cleanup and certbot's
      own renewal timer plus a deploy hook for certificate renewals.
  * Security:
    - Remove the fqdncredmgrd socket daemon; credentials are read directly
      from the root-only SQLite DB (/var/lib/a2tools/creds.db, 0600).
    - Provider API credentials are no longer passed on the curl command
      line (were visible in the process list); request bodies are sent via
      stdin.
    - Move the shared cache from the predictable world-writable /tmp path
      to /var/cache/a2tools (prevents local cache poisoning of root's DNS
      verification).
    - Validate WAN IP lookups (HTTPS, timeout, strict IPv4 check); state
      is stored in /var/lib/a2tools instead of mutating /etc/environment.
    - Consistent SQL escaping for all sqlite interpolations; FQDN
      validation at all entry points.
    - fqdncredmgr can read API keys from stdin (-p -); passing the key as a
      command-line argument is no longer supported. Interactive prompts use
      systemd-ask-password (masked) with a read fallback.
  * Robustness:
    - Shared library (lib/common.sh); libraries no longer set shell
      options or traps in the sourcing script. The getinput library was
      dropped entirely in favor of the read builtin and
      systemd-ask-password; interactive prompts no longer time out.
    - fqdnmgr output works without a TTY (certbot hooks under timers).
    - a2certrenew is now a thin wrapper over `certbot renew` (fixes lost
      renewal counters and abort-on-first-failure).
    - Configuration consolidated under /etc/a2tools; databases and state
      under /var/lib/a2tools.

 -- Amine Tbaik <tbaik.amine@gmail.com>  Sun, 05 Jul 2026 00:00:00 +0000

